body:
I'm trying to leverage osxcross https://github.com/tpoechtrager/osxcross and compile for OSX target on linux.

despite getting the right toolchain in place, it seems there's still a few things missing, could anyone shine some light?

- got osxcross
- got clang/gcc in place in osxcross
- got a working copy of python 3.6.9 from osx 

referred to some docs in https://stackoverflow.com/questions/38388812/using-cython-to-cross-compile-project-from-intel-ubuntu-to-arm
etc

comment_data.body:
I seem to have to be able to get a manual compile going:

```
x86_64-apple-darwin12-clang -I /root/cross/3.6.9/include/python3.6m/ -Wno-unused-result -Wsign-compare -Wunreachable-code -DNDEBUG -g -fwrapv -O3 -Wall -c result.c -o result.o
x86_64-apple-darwin12-clang -I /root/cross/3.6.9/include/python3.6m/ -bundle -undefined dynamic_lookup -L/root/cross/3.6.9/lib result.o -o result.so
```

but i only could achieve that by looking at a compile output using cythonize in osx, and recreating that command but use clang from osxcross instead.

is there a set of arguments I need to set in order to tell cythonize/distutils/setuptools to use the above options instead of the other madness?

seem to have made... some more progress, hacking out `distutils.sysconfig.get_config_vars()` to use the values from an OSX machine gets me a bit further ahead:
